trend_summary: Built-up footprint roughly doubled, with scattered pockets coalescing into larger suburban clusters along new and upgraded roads. Housing subdivisions radiate from the central spine, while forest and pasture shrink at edges. Industrial or commercial pads emerge near highway interchanges. Overall fabric stays green-dominated, but built form spreads steadily in all directions.
notable_changes: North-west quadrant shows new highway/overpass and adjacent commercial pads
Central corridor infilled with cul-de-sac housing, reducing forest gaps
South-central quarry/industrial site expands and brightens visibly
Eastern edge farmland converted to residential tracts and road grid
